This problem describes a spiral laid out on a hexagonal grid. We must first determine the pattern of the spiral and identify the coordinates of the number $N=2026$.

We rely on the standard properties of hexagonal spirals:
1. The number of cells in layer $L_k$ is $6k$.
2. The total number of cells up to layer $L_k$ is $N(k) = 1 + 3k(k+1)$.

We find the layer $k$ containing $N=2026$.
$N(25) = 1 + 3(25)(26) = 1951$.
$N(26) = 1951 + 6(26) = 1951 + 156 = 2107$.
$2026$ is in layer $L_{26}$, so $k=26$. $2026$ is $M = 2026 - 1951 = 75$ steps into $L_{26}$.

$L_{26}$ has 6 segments, each of length $k=26$. $75 = 2 \times 26 + 23$.
$2026$ is the $23^{\text{rd}}$ number in the third segment ($S_3$).

We use cube coordinates $(x, y, z)$ with $x+y+z=0$. The distance from the center (1) is $d = \max(|x|, |y|, |z|)$. Directions are defined by the 6 basis vectors $V_i$.
$V_0=(1, -1, 0), V_1=(1, 0, -1), V_2=(0, 1, -1), V_3=(-1, 1, 0), V_4=(-1, 0, 1), V_5=(0, -1, 1)$.

Assuming a regular spiral progression where the segment direction sequence is $V_2, V_3, V_4, V_5, V_0, V_1$ (which guarantees movement along the perimeter $d=k$):
$P_{k}$ starts $L_k$. $P_{k} = C_5(k) = (k, -k, 0)$.

For $k=26$: $P_{1952} = C_5(26) = (26, -26, 0)$. This is the starting point of $L_{26}$.
$S_1$ (26 steps $V_2$): ends at $P_{1978} = C_0(26) = (26, 0, -26)$.
$S_2$ (26 steps $V_3$): ends at $P_{2004} = C_1(26) = (0, 26, -26)$.
$S_3$ starts at $P_{2004}$. Direction $V_4$.
$P(2026) = P(2004) + 22 V_4$. (Since 2026 is $23^{\text{rd}}$ number, it is 22 steps after the start).
$P(2026) = (0, 26, -26) + 22 (-1, 0, 1) = (-22, 26, -4)$.

We seek the sum of the 6 neighbors of 2026. $P = (-22, 26, -4)$. The neighbors are $P+V_i$.

1. Spiral neighbors (on $L_{26}$, direction $V_4$):
$N_4 = 2027$: $P+V_4 = (-23, 26, -3)$. (23 steps in $S_3$).
$N_1 = 2025$: $P-V_4 = P+V_1$. $P+V_1 = (-21, 26, -5)$. (21 steps in $S_3$).

2. Neighbors on $L_{25}$ (k=25):
$N_0 = P+V_0 = (-21, 25, -4)$. $L_{25}$ starts at $N(24)+1 = 1796$. $P(1846) = C_1(25) = (0, 25, -25)$. $S_3$ direction $V_4$.
$P(N_0) - P(1846) = (-21, 0, 21) = 21 V_4$. $j=21$.
$N_0 = 1846 + 21 = 1867$.

$N_5 = P+V_5 = (-22, 25, -3)$. $P(N_5) - P(1846) = (-22, 0, 22) = 22 V_4$. $j=22$.
$N_5 = 1846 + 22 = 1868$.

3. Neighbors on $L_{27}$ (k=27):
$N_2 = P+V_2 = (-22, 27, -5)$. $L_{27}$ starts at $2108$. $P(2162) = C_1(27) = (0, 27, -27)$. $S_3$ direction $V_4$.
$P(N_2) - P(2162) = (-22, 0, 22) = 22 V_4$. $j=22$.
$N_2 = 2162 + 22 = 2184$.

$N_3 = P+V_3 = (-23, 27, -4)$. $P(N_3) - P(2162) = (-23, 0, 23) = 23 V_4$. $j=23$.
$N_3 = 2162 + 23 = 2185$.

The sum of neighbors is:
$S = 2025 + 2027 + 1867 + 1868 + 2184 + 2185$
$S = 4052 + 3735 + 4369$
$S = 12156$.

The sum of all 6 neighbors of the number 2026 is 12156.
